The paper proposes a method for seismic facies recognition based on prestack seismic data using a convolutional autoencoder network for deep feature learning. This approach is similar to image clustering problems in computer vision, suggesting that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves data processing and feature extraction, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques for classification and clustering also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper involves information retrieval and pattern recognition, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves signal processing and analysis, which could fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
